Center A - Week 10 of 2023 Report

This report details the key performance indicators for Center A during the week of March 6th to March

12th, 2023.

Patient Volume and Care:

Center A served a total of 4,200 patients during this period. The average time for patients to be served

was 28 minutes. Analyzing the data based on urgency levels, patients categorized as "Urgent" waited

an average of 7 minutes, "Semi-Urgent" patients waited 20 minutes, and "Non-Urgent" patients waited

an average of 32 minutes. Patient satisfaction scores averaged 3, indicating a potential need for

improvement in patient experience.

Operational Efficiency:

The number of readmissions for the week was 35, suggesting potential areas for improvement in

post-discharge care. 106 medical licenses were presented, ensuring proper staff credentialing. A total

of 501 staff training hours were dedicated to enhancing skills and knowledge. The utilization rate of

equipment and resources was 60%, indicating a potential opportunity to optimize resource allocation.

Center A ordered and consumed 8,224 supplies, highlighting the high volume of patient care provided.

The turnover rate of staff stood at 7%, which is within the acceptable range.

Financial Performance and Outpatient Services:

The average cost per patient was $696. Center A saw 2,962 outpatient appointments, showcasing a

strong commitment to community health. There were 470 emergency room visits, indicating a high

demand for acute care services. 210 surgical procedures were performed, reflecting the center's

capability in surgical interventions. The bed occupancy rate was 70%, demonstrating high utilization of

available resources. This week, due to the winter season, there was a slight increase in bed

occupancy, reaching 76%.
